The artifact is downloading, but your path to the dacpac is wrong.

Right now your deploy step looks for:

```powershell
$(Pipeline.Workspace)\database.dacpac
```

But `DownloadBuildArtifacts@0` with:

```yaml
artifactName: 'db-drop'
downloadPath: '$(Pipeline.Workspace)'
```

downloads into a subfolder named after the artifact, so the file is usually here:

```powershell
$(Pipeline.Workspace)\db-drop\database.dacpac
```

Sometimes it can also be nested one level deeper depending on what was published, so the safest fix is to search for the dacpac.

## Fix in `deploy-database.yml`

Replace this:

```yaml
- powershell: |
    $dacpac = "$(Pipeline.Workspace)\database.dacpac"

    if (!(Test-Path $dacpac)) {
      throw "database.dacpac not found at: $dacpac"
    }

    & "${{ parameters.sqlPackagePath }}" /Action:Publish `
      /SourceFile:"$dacpac" `
      /TargetConnectionString:"${{ parameters.targetConnectionString }}" `
      ${{ parameters.sqlPackageArgs }}

    if ($LASTEXITCODE -ne 0) { exit $LASTEXITCODE }
  displayName: 'Publish database'
```

with this:

```yaml
- powershell: |
    Write-Host "Pipeline.Workspace = $(Pipeline.Workspace)"
    Write-Host "Artifact name = ${{ parameters.artifactName }}"

    Get-ChildItem "$(Pipeline.Workspace)" -Recurse | Select-Object FullName

    $dacpac = Get-ChildItem "$(Pipeline.Workspace)\${{ parameters.artifactName }}" -Recurse -Filter database.dacpac |
              Select-Object -First 1

    if (-not $dacpac) {
      throw "database.dacpac not found under $(Pipeline.Workspace)\${{ parameters.artifactName }}"
    }

    Write-Host "Using dacpac: $($dacpac.FullName)"

    & "${{ parameters.sqlPackagePath }}" /Action:Publish `
      /SourceFile:"$($dacpac.FullName)" `
      /TargetConnectionString:"${{ parameters.targetConnectionString }}" `
      ${{ parameters.sqlPackageArgs }}

    if ($LASTEXITCODE -ne 0) { exit $LASTEXITCODE }
  displayName: 'Publish database'
```

## Why this happens

In build, you publish this folder:

```yaml
PathtoPublish: '${{ parameters.outputFolder }}'
ArtifactName: '${{ parameters.artifactName }}'
```

So Azure DevOps stores the contents under the artifact name, and when you download it, the files are not placed directly at the root of `$(Pipeline.Workspace)`.

## Also check this

Your message shows both templates merged into one pasted block. Make sure `build-database-project.yml` and `deploy-database.yml` are actually **separate files** in the templates repo. The deploy template should not contain the build template content above it in the same file unless that is intentional.

## Final expected path

With your current settings, the likely real path is:

```text
C:\agent\_work\7\db-drop\database.dacpac
```

not:

```text
C:\agent\_work\7\database.dacpac
```

So the immediate fix is to search under `$(Pipeline.Workspace)\${{ parameters.artifactName }}`.
